    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just the physical pain though. it's the mental drain of knowing tomorrow is just going to be the exact same thing. every morning i wake up and i'm already grieving the day before it's even happened. i'm just so tired of fighting a war that i've already lost. it feels less like living and more like just... enduring.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
